cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with action recognition using ConvNets. The paper also proposes an end-to-end trainable gated fusion method, which involves learning the gating fusion weights and the gating ConvNet, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses the MoE (Mixture of Experts) theory, which is a popular approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for combining multiple models. The paper also deals with video data, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new multi-task learning method, which involves jointly learning multiple tasks, indicating that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
